## Entities (Innermost Circle)

### Rule: No Framework Dependencies

Domain must be pure — no framework annotations, no database knowledge.

```java
// ❌ BAD - Framework annotations in entity
@Entity
@Table(name = "orders")
public class Order {
  @Id private UUID id;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Pure entity
public class Order {
  private final OrderId id;
  private OrderStatus status;
  // No framework annotations
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - ORM decorator in entity
@Entity()
export class User {
  @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()
  id: string;
}

// ✅ GOOD - Plain class
export class User {
  readonly id: UserId;
  readonly email: Email;
}
```

### Factory Methods

```java
public class Order {
  private final OrderId id;
  private OrderStatus status;
  private final List<OrderLine> lines;
  
  // Private constructor - use factory method
  private Order(OrderId id, OrderStatus status) {
    this.id = Objects.requireNonNull(id);
    this.status = status;
    this.lines = new ArrayList<>();
  }
  
  // Factory for new orders
  public static Order create() {
    return new Order(OrderId.generate(), OrderStatus.DRAFT);
  }
  
  // Reconstitution from persistence
  public static Order reconstitute(OrderId id, OrderStatus status, List<OrderLine> lines) {
    Order order = new Order(id, status);
    order.lines.addAll(lines);
    return order;
  }
  
  // Business logic in entity
  public void place() {
    if (lines.isEmpty()) throw new OrderException.EmptyOrder();
    this.status = OrderStatus.PLACED;
  }
}
```

### Immutable Value Objects

```java
// ✅ GOOD - Immutable value object
public record Money(BigDecimal amount, Currency currency) {
  public Money {
    Objects.requireNonNull(amount);
    Objects.requireNonNull(currency);
  }
  
  public Money add(Money other) {
    if (!this.currency.equals(other.currency))
      throw new CurrencyMismatchException();
    return new Money(this.amount.add(other.amount), this.currency);
  }
}
```

