## Key Principles

### Data Structure Crossing Boundaries

Pass simple data structures across boundaries, never domain entities.

```java
// ✅ GOOD - Input/Output data structures cross boundaries
public PlaceOrderOutput execute(PlaceOrderInput input) { /* ... */ }

// ❌ BAD - Domain entity crosses boundary
public void process(Order order) { /* ... */ }
```

### Dependency Inversion

```
                    UseCase
                       │
            ┌──────────┴──────────┐
            │  OrderGateway      │  ← Interface in use case circle
            └──────────┬──────────┘
                       │
                 JpaOrderGateway  ← Implementation in framework circle
```

### Composition Root

Wire dependencies in one place.

```java
@Configuration
class AppConfig {
  @Bean
  public OrderGateway orderGateway(JpaOrderRepository repository) {
    return repository;
  }
  
  @Bean
  public PlaceOrderUseCase placeOrderUseCase(OrderGateway gateway, ProductGateway productGateway) {
    return new PlaceOrderUseCaseImpl(gateway, productGateway);
  }
}
```

---

## Architecture Checklist

- [ ] Entities circle has no framework annotations
- [ ] Use case interfaces define application behavior
- [ ] Source code dependencies point inward only
- [ ] Entities use factory methods (private constructors)
- [ ] Value Objects are immutable
- [ ] Business logic in entities/use cases
- [ ] Gateways implement interfaces defined in use case circle
- [ ] Simple data structures cross boundaries
- [ ] All database/SQL code in outermost circle
- [ ] Composition root wires all dependencies

